<div id="review_2492437935" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2492437935" />
    <a title="Stephen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4809022-stephen"><img alt="Stephen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1295019472p2/4809022.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2492437935?book_show_action=true">Aug 26, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephen" href="/user/show/4809022-stephen">Stephen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4809022-stephen?shelf=favourites-non-fiction">favourites-non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4809022-stephen?shelf=my-top-5-books-read-in-2018">my-top-5-books-read-in-2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2492437935" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18409675789974974125">This was one of those books that was so good that it not only got me interested in Stonewall Jackson but also in the Civil War in general. While reading it, I have also been watching the documentary &quot;The Civil War&quot; from 1990 which was mentioned in one of the reviews of this book on Goodreads - 9 episodes of over an hour each (some an hour and a half) that I found fascinating and is well worth investing the time in:<br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MCdtW69Eqng&amp;list=PLXKLYIH9Cw8viQePDMdNf8yn3l3pKJkEc'>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MCdtW...</a><br/><br/>Returning to the book itself, it was one o</span>
  <span id="freeText18409675789974974125" style="display:none">This was one of those books that was so good that it not only got me interested in Stonewall Jackson but also in the Civil War in general. While reading it, I have also been watching the documentary "The Civil War" from 1990 which was mentioned in one of the reviews of this book on Goodreads - 9 episodes of over an hour each (some an hour and a half) that I found fascinating and is well worth investing the time in:<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MCdtW69Eqng&amp;list=PLXKLYIH9Cw8viQePDMdNf8yn3l3pKJkEc">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MCdtW...</a><br /><br />Returning to the book itself, it was one of the best biographies that I have ever read - you really felt like you knew the man by the end and what an extraordinary man he was. A man of God who completely believed that any success was down to God rather than to him personally yet who was totally ruthless and very aggressive in his battle tactics, in contrast to the succession of cautious Union generals that he defeated. A hero to the South whose army was prevailing against overwhelming odds until he died and the succession of David v Goliath wins makes this a really engaging read. The great victories were all ones that he fought in and everything seemed to go wrong once he was no longer around (Gettysburg happened soon after). Amazing that one man was so critical to a whole war, in no small way thanks to the legend that built up around him as much as to his skills as a general.<br /><br />A great introduction to the Civil War but also surely the most extensive biography of Stonewall Jackson that has been or will ever be written. Next I'm going to read Shelby Foote (he features extensively in the Civil War documentary mentioned above)'s trilogy about the Civil War - thousands more pages but I'm hooked now. Anyway, after reading the book and watching the series, I think that knowing about the Civil War is essential in understanding American history since then as well as what is happening now so there's really no choice for anyone that is interested in that.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="18409675789974974125" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2492437935">
  <td colspan="2">
